author: gdaniels
msg: Refactoring service descriptors, take 1.  ServiceDesc changes to be
an interface, and the code that was there to introspect Java classes,
etc now lives in JavaServiceDesc.  Places that care about Java-specific
things look for the class, places that only need the generic stuff use
Also a few cosmetic changes in this commit, and change the way wrapped
parameters are written so that arrays become "maxOccurs='unbounded'"
instead of SOAP encoded arrays (inappropriate for doc/lit!).
